In this article, the White House Office of the Press Secretary shares a weekly message from President Barack Obama. The message focuses on the holiday season and emphasizes the importance of recognizing our common humanity and values. The President highlights the celebrations of Passover and Easter and mentions that while people practice their faith in different ways, we all share the same spirit of humanity. He urges everyone to remember the importance of work, health, education, and community, which are fundamental to all major religions. The President also mentions the positive news of job growth in the economy but acknowledges that there is still much work to be done to recover from the recession. He emphasizes the value of health and education, as well as the aspirations for a fulfilling and purposeful life. The President concludes by urging unity and love for one another, referencing a sermon delivered by a chaplain during World War II. He wishes everyone a Happy Easter and Passover.